ionWorkspacePage.tsx:2155:                        'No active composition job is available to redirect.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2180:                      previewStage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2188:                      controlId: 'composition-return-to-plan',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2217:                    setPreviewStage('composition')\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2220:                      stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2223:                      valueSummary: `Revisit composition for segment ${segmentIndex}`,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2240:                    setPreviewStage('composition')\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2243:                      stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2244:                      controlId: 'finalize-return-to-composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2378:                hint={`Resume at ${getWorkflowStageLabel(snapshot.resume_stage)} with ${progress.percent}% of the workflow currently complete.`}\ndocs/system-diagram.md:3:This diagram shows the intended runtime shape for Storyteller after the core session, worker, and realtime prompts are built. It documents where session resume, durable event history, realtime delivery, and long-running jobs belong.\ndocs/system-diagram.md:10:    Worker[\"Worker process<br/>composition jobs, audio jobs, retries, interruption\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:16:    API -->|\"resume session snapshot\"| Browser\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\"planning, composition, TTS calls\"| Gemini\ndocs/domain-model.md:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\ndocs/domain-model.md:23:| `resume_stage` | Earliest stage that still needs work when a session is reopened. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:38:`resume_stage` is the key anti-guessing field. The backend computes it from durable stage states so the frontend does not need to infer where to reopen a session by looking at which panels happen to have data.\ndocs/domain-model.md:50:| `workflow_stage_state` | Per-stage state for the session. | `session_id`, `stage`, `status`, `updated_at`, `last_event_id`. | Stored explicitly so resume does not depend on sparse child tables. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:121:- If all stages are `completed`, `resume_stage` is `finalize`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:123:This is the behavior implemented by the `resolve_resume_stage` helper in both the backend and frontend contract files.\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:164:   - Result: open the session on `resume_stage = pitches`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:170:   - Result: open on `resume_stage = finalize`, but still allow explicit navigation back to earlier stages for edits.\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:149:  resume_stage: 'beats',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:229:      stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:379:  active_composition_job: null,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:461:          'The current focus is softening the midpoint before composition starts.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:538:      source_stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:710:      : stage === 'composition'\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:711:        ? 'composition'\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:852:      current_stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:853:      resume_stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:930:      r