ion/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:5816:      hydration: resumedHydration,\nbackend/app/services/agent_context.py:25:            f\"Resume stage: {snapshot.resume_stage.value}\",\nbackend/app/services/agent_context.py:105:    composition_job = snapshot.active_composition_job or snapshot.latest_composition_job\nbackend/app/services/agent_context.py:106:    if composition_job is not None:\nbackend/app/services/agent_context.py:109:            f\"{composition_job.status} at \"\nbackend/app/services/agent_context.py:110:            f\"{composition_job.progress_percent:.1f}%\"\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:3:The composition runtime now treats each outline card as a durable writing segment and carries\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:11:   - Re-assembles the composition prompt package for the active outline card.\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:21:The runtime stores this carryover under `composition_segments.payload.context_carryover` so later\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:35:Each `composition_segments` row now stores:\ndocs/segmented-writing-context-carryover.md:43:The object-storage side also keeps a `composition_segment` asset per completed segment revision,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:4:The goal is to make session history durable enough for replay, resume debugging,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:31:| `content.user_edit.recorded` | Structured user-authored edits to durable planning or composition records. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:59:  \"resume_stage\": \"pitches\",\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:96:- `record_composition_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxo