{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"agent_message","text":"The existing model already has an explicit `draft_text_snapshot` asset kind, but the main draft loop never writes it. That gives a clean path: use the existing asset vocabulary instead of inventing a new one, then tighten snapshot assembly so resume can prefer the latest durable checkpoint over volatile in-memory metadata."}}
